defaultIntroductiondefault1. 
defaultThe National Children’s Bureau and Council for Disabled Children welcome
default the Education Select Committee’s inquiry on the under-achieveme
defaultnt in education by working class children.  
defaultThere are
default a wide range of factors, both within and outside the school environment, which are having a deleterious effect on the 
defaulteducational attainment of children and young people from disadvantaged families.   
defaultThe Centre for Social Justice’s recent report ‘
defaultRequires Improvement: the causes of educational failure’
default highlights the critical need to gain a better understanding of why white working class children, and in particular boys, are falling behind their peers
default and not meeting their full potential. 
